</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SARA LEE, the international consumer products group, expects its capital
expenditures in the 1993 fiscal year to exceed Dollars 700m, up from Dollars
509m in 1992, according to Mr John Bryan, chairman, Reuter reports from
Chicago.
Mr Bryan said after Sara Lee's annual meeting that most of the increase
would go toward vertical integration of manufacturing capacity for its
personal products. It would also increase manufacturing capacity for
products including knitwear, which saw a 13 per cent unit volume growth in
the first quarter ended September 26.
Sara Lee's capital spending would exceed its previous peak of Dollars 593m
posted in 1990, he said.
Sara Lee is in negotiations in Mexico and Europe to expand its packaged meat
business overseas. The move could come through acquisitions or joint
ventures, he said.
