<HEADLINE>
FT  29 OCT 92 / UK Company News: Majedie asset value declines to 338p
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over the 12 months ended September 30 net asset value of Majedie Investments
fell from 348p to 338p.
However, on the revenue side earnings improved.
Directors said their generally cautious approach proved to be advantageous
in a period of volatility in the currency and securities markets.
Investment income came to Pounds 4.56m (Pounds 4.53m) and earnings per share
worked through at 10.07p (9.81p).
The final dividend is 7p, for a total of 9.5p (9p) and a 1-for-1 scrip issue
is proposed.
