</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TWO recently floated companies
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Dorling Kindersley Holdings, the international publishing group, and JD
Wetherspoon, the chain of 44 Greater London pubs - yesterday announced the
results of their offers to financial intermediaries.
The 7m Dorling Kindersley shares offered to the public at 165p were six
times subscribed. Strong demand for the shares had already caused the amount
on offer through intermediates to be increased from 25 to 36.3 per cent of
the issue, valuing the group at Pounds 101.7m.
In the JD Wetherspoon flotation, which valued the group at Pounds 45.6m,
