intermediaries. The remainder of the 14.68m shares on offer have been placed
with institutions, raising a total of Pounds 24m.
Dorling Kindersley said investors who had applied for 5m or more shares
would receive 10 per cent of the number sought; those who applied for
between 2m and 4.99m would receive 15 per cent and those who sought fewer
than 2m would be allocated 21.95 per cent, rounded to the nearest 100
shares.
A further 12.15m shares were firmly placed with institutions last Friday.
The flotation raised Pounds 31.6m, of which Pounds 25m was new money for the
company.
