<TEXT>
BLACKS LEISURE, the camping goods and sportswear company, reported a 74 per
cent fall in pre-tax profits in the six months to August 29 after its retail
division incurred its first ever loss.
Pre-tax profits fell from Pounds 2.21m to Pounds 580,000 on sales ahead to
Pounds 35.1m (Pounds 33.8m).
The interim dividend is cut to 0.75p (1.1p), payable from earnings of 1.68p
(6.41p) per share. Mr Simon Bentley, chairman and chief executive, said the
decision reflected uncertain expectations of the second half. The company
intends to maintain the dividend at its new level.
