yesterday fell another 7p to 32p.
A lack of consumer confidence and competitive price cutting adversely
affected the retail operation which incurred a deficit before interest and
tax of Pounds 89,000 compared with profits of Pounds 1.1m.
The outcome included an exceptional profit of Pounds 185,000 related to the
sale of the High Wycombe site.
Mr Bentley warned that the effective devaluation of sterling would make
things worse because the division imports much of its sports footwear.
The distribution operation saw pre-tax profits fall from Pounds 2.35m to
Pounds 1.72m. Mr Bentley said the decline in consumer spending was mainly
responsible for the fall.
S Eker, the textile converting and merchanting operation, was closed and
shown as an extraordinary charge of Pounds 8.8m, including Pounds 7.7m of
goodwill already written off.
Gearing fell from 37 per cent to 31 per cent.
