FT  29 OCT 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: Bauxite output down in Jamaica
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CANUTE JAMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KINGSTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JAMAICA'S bauxite (alumin-ium ore) production in the third quarter of this
year was 2.87m tonnes, 6.2 per cent less than in the corresponding quarter
of 1991.
The Jamaica Bauxite Institute, the state agency that monitors the industry,
said export of crude bauxite in the third quarter was 1.09m tonnes, 10 per
cent less than in the third quarter of 1991. Third-quarter exports of
alumina (aluminium oxide) fell 1.7 per cent to 728,781 tonnes.
The declines in production and exports were caused mainly by the termination
late last year of a contract to supply 1m tonnes of ore a year to the former
Soviet Union.
