GENERAL Dynamics, the US defence group which has been selling off large
parts of its businesses, has put its jet fighter division on the auction
block, according to union officials. Wall Street analysts believe it could
fetch Dollars 1bn or more.
The company declined to comment, but such a move would represent a
substantial change of strategy by the group's management, which had
identified fighter aircraft as one of four core businesses it intended to
retain.
